BUT -  I do it anyways, and I have never regretted it.  A little prayer and I am back on track.<br>
<br>
I'm not any different from you just because I'm Christian, you know.  I'm still a normal person who makes mistakes.  I just have someone else to turn to, someone else to count on, someone who loves me perfectly, someone whose word gives me meaning and guidance....  and I can't ever mess it up and it was given to me freely and its a perfect love that shall never ever fail me.  It doesn't mean I always do the right thing or give selflessly all the time or let people beat me and my kid up... I react just like you would and just like Sally Brown next door.  I just have this added bonus to my life that I can choose to appropriate for myself.  I have a different focus in life is one way you could put it.  Christ - focused.  Whereas most people are self - focused.  hope that made sense to you. <br>
